com.nokia.places

Interface Content

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Editorial, Image, Review

    public interface Content
    This interface represents the basis for additional rich content about a Place.

    The following specialized content may be available:

    • images
    • editorials
    • reviews


    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - Media collections

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      RichText getAttributionText()
      This method retrieves a ready-to-display text string that attributes the content to a source according to the terms and conditions.
      Supplier getSupplier()
      This method retrieves a link to the resource representing the supplier of the content (the object provides details on the origin of the information).
      java.lang.String getSupplierName()
      This method retrieves the name of the supplier
      java.lang.String getType()
      This method retrieves the specialized content type.
      ExternalLink getViaLink()
      This method retrieves a link to the origin of the information, typically a website of the supplier.

    • Method Detail

      • getAttributionText

        RichText getAttributionText()
        This method retrieves a ready-to-display text string that attributes the content to a source according to the terms and conditions.

        For more information about source attribution, refer to Nokia's Restful Places API - Source Attribution.

        Returns:
        The RichText attribution for the content source.

      • getSupplier

        Supplier getSupplier()
        This method retrieves a link to the resource representing the supplier of the content (the object provides details on the origin of the information).
        Returns:
        The SupplierLink to the content supplier.

      • getViaLink

        ExternalLink getViaLink()
        This method retrieves a link to the origin of the information, typically a website of the supplier.
        Returns:
        An ExternalLink to the information origin.

      • getType

        java.lang.String getType()
        This method retrieves the specialized content type.
        Returns:
        The ContentType representing the specialized content type.

      • getSupplierName

        java.lang.String getSupplierName()
        This method retrieves the name of the supplier
        Returns:
        The name of the supplier of this content
